After verification of the specificity of hybridomas producing mAbPEDV by WB analysis, ELISA and IP detection of PEDV antigen in infected and non-infected cells, three preparations (3C8/2H6; C2/D5; 2B7) were selected for further use. All were of the isotype IgG1 and reacted with the membrane protein M (Mr 20–30 K) in WB analysis (Fig. 1
). ELISA titres of mAbPEDV solutions containing 4 mg Ig/ml ranged between 64,000 and 1,024,000. The mixtures of the same concentrations (w/v) of all three mAb (conjugated or unconjugated) were used in blocking ELISA examinations. Cross reactivity with other viral antigens could not be detected using any of the methods mentioned (Table 2
; group of samples 1).
